< text>
The freshest avocados are here. Tomatoes too! I've only had the tacos here & they are damn tasty. Fresh ingredients, food is filling, reasonable prices & the service is among the absolute finest, not just at Grand Central, but in all of L.A. The lovely sincere woman who usually helps me is so attentive to the details of my order, I always feel appreciated as a customer, feeling a bit more uplifted than when I came in.<//text>

Great bang for your buck taco place.  The line was a bit long but we go through in no time, and everything was delicious.  The Asada were definitely my favorite and their salsas were very good.  We also ordered a side of Guacamole which was super delicious.  We did not leave hungry!< /Text>

< Review>
The server was excellent, very attentive, never kept our 3 women group waiting.  The menu was extensive, with breakfast served all day, ranging from burgers to steaks to tacos and enchiladas, and taquitos.  I was hard-pressed to make a choice!  My friends enjoyed salads with incredibly fresh vegetables.  I chose a cinnamon roll French toast, and I didn't like it as much as I thought I would.  Come to Brandon's Diner for a great "Home-Made" meal. By the way, they were well set up to serve during this pandemic, with social distancing and other precautions taken as required.<//Review>

<Name>Sam Sager</Name><Date>1589342939857< /Date>< Rate>
5< /Rate>
< review>
Brandon's has been a local staple for at least 30 years. The place is like home! It started off with the amazing pancakes and omelettes and world class biscuits and gravy. Then not too long after Brandon's got it's start, new owners came along. That's a scary thing. . . But not this time. They kept the old classics exactly the way they were. (Man, that gravy is good!) And we got something new with it. Some pretty incredible Mexican food. The heuvos rancheros is the best I've ever had. The one I compare all others too. It's unique too, they use chili Verde instead of a red sauce. Taco Tuesday's are definitely a hit. If you haven't given this place a shot, it's about time you do!<//review>

< text>
Coming from a family that eats at this location almost every Tuesday...We know we will receive good customer service and great food. However on May 7th, my family and I had the worst experience in my entire life. The food was good but the service was terrible. The first check was paid by a card. Easy enough...first one done. And then she asked us for the second check and again not hiding her frustration at all, we said we were paying cash for the next two. We began to list the items on the second check and she rudely interrupted asking who was going to pay for the third. There was three of us there. We showed $10 for the second bill and and $50 for the third. But she kept repeating who was going to pay for the third atleast three times. Even though there was three of us, she was not ok with one person holding the $10 in one had and $50 in the other. And SANDRA kept repeating "who's paying for the third receipt. < review>
This location is large and has lots of seating. It also has a drive through.

They are less busy here after the morning rush. So, it makes for a nice spot to have meetings, study or work. They are more crowded on weekends.

During my visits the crew was friendly, efficient and accurate with my orders. They also carry the new Nitro Brew if you are looking to try it.

Overall, I like this location and will be back in the future.<//review>

<Rate>5<//Rate>< Text>
WOW! I never write reviews but I felt compelled to share my amazing experience at the Whittier location yesterday. From the very beginning, my sister and I felt very welcomed by the hospitable staff. There was even a cute message board outside that said "Welcome Carmela" in the front. My stylist was Shawna and she was the best. I felt like she truly listened to what I wanted in a dress, wasn't pushy, and gave me genuine honest feedback on how the dresses fit on me. She made me feel comfortable the whole time- unlike other places, where you can tell they're just desperate to make a sale. G+G also had a wider variety of dresses to choose from at more affordable prices. They even have a deal where you can get$200 off if you purchase the dress on your first visit. At other boutiques I went to, I felt like the dresses looked like leftover prom dresses being sold at inflated prices. But not at G+G. I was able to find the sleek, elegant & timeless dress I was looking for. Overall, the entire experience here was so worth it and I'm glad I found G+G. The only thing I wish I knew beforehand was that at purchase, they offer packages ranging from $99-380 for dress cleaning/storage/preservation and alteration. So definitely keep that in mind when you go to get your dress. Ultimately, I loved this place! Thanks G+G and Shawna! :)<//Text>

<Review>I am so glad my friend told me about this hidden gem! The moment I walked in, I felt like it was my playground!! <rate>5<//rate><Gmap_id>0x80c2d495d1f4235d:0x77d289189d522e0a</Gmap_id>< Review>
Although this was not the first bridal shop that I went searching through for my dress, I am so happy it was my last. I had walked in on a Saturday and it was super busy. Claudia was very kind in making an appointment for me the following day. I went first thing Sunday morning with my mom and we picked out some dresses that we liked. Sarah was phenomenal. She was so helpful and "warm" (for lack of a better word). I was a bit nervous at first with the fact that she was in there helping me in and out of dresses, but she made me feel very comfortable. We tried out quite a few dresses and she was not shy about giving me her opinions on them...something I value very much. Once I picked out my top three she even had me try them out with all the trimmings...veil, flowers, etc. We left satisfied and went to go get a second opinion from dad. He wanted to see it in person so we went back later that day. Seeing the full effect nearly brought him to tears, and that was all I needed to see to know that I had found MY dress. They even gave me that giddy experience afterwards of taking pictures of me saying "yes" to the dress. Brilliant doesn't even begin to do this bridal shop justice.

There were beautiful dresses there in all types of styles. The ladies there were very helpful and friendly and take pride in the work they do. There was never any pressure or sales pitch. The prices and services speak for themselves.< /Review>

<Time>1449289133220</Time><gmap_id>0x8099900ea9316813:0x8804e16eaeea8e12< /gmap_id><pics>None<//pics><user_name>Paul</user_name><userid>107803583590832108073</userid>< Text>
Went here during our resort stay and we were very happy with the service and food. It is nice that it is attached to the resort. Also, our waitress allowed us to use the happy hour menu in the main dining area instead of having to sit in the bar area.

Pros:
1) Wide variety of happy hour items from 4-6pm every day (fish tacos were yummy!)
2) Good location inside of Lake Tahoe Vacation resort
3) Friendly service
4) Got a coupon for a free Peach Cobbler from the concierge which was delicious!

Cons:
1) We went a little early in the evening and the service was a little slow (one waitress for three tables in the dining area)
2) The 6" pizza appetizer tasted good, but was comparable to a frozen pizza you buy at the grocery store (my wife liked it, but I wasn't the biggest fan)
3) You have to go through the pool area to use the closest bathroom (be careful if it is during the winter because the floor is really slippery)<//Text>

<userid>104034107678828056082< /userid><user_name>Austin Gonsalves<//user_name><time>1559443908661</time><Rating>1<//Rating>< Text>
My fiance and I attempted to book a large dinner reservation for the weekend of our wedding to have dinner with our families who live all over the country. We saw the photos of the food and menu and looked like a good choic . We called and left a message, then received a call back saying the main room was reserved, but the patio and another room were available, but required a deposit to reserve. He stated he would email us prices, we end up reciveing a catering menu and price sheet, we call back and state we weren't looking to hold an event or gathering, just wanting to place a reservation for a large dinner instead. Their response was they cant book large parties because they depend on high table turnovers. Which baffles me because a group of 35 people spending an average of $25+ a person plus tip and gratuity, not to mention drinks would overcome the cost of taking up a few tables for a couple of hours at most. Definitly will not be a patron of this establishment and will not be giving this buisness our money.< /Text>

5</Rate>
< Review>
I rarely post reviews for products online as I'm seldom impressed with a product enough to do so.  However, in this instance I feel compelled to shout this one from the rooftops!  I am the full time caregiver for my 64 spouse who I've been married to for 46 years.  She has Type II diabetes among other serious maladies, but her blood sugar drops dangerously low without warning, often in her sleep.  With the new Libre II device monitoring her levels in real time and sounding the alarm, we are able to promptly react before she goes into hypoglycemic shock.  Just as amazing is the predictive nature of the device that forecasts rising or falling trends of her lab values thus allowing us to adjust diet and other factors resulting using less insulin.  It is a game changer for us!  Finally, we are so grateful to Advanced Diabetes Supply for guiding us through the process of obtaining the device, coordinating medical records, insurance company requirements and keeping us posted every step of the way!  We dealt with a person by the name of Izzy who was professional, compassionate and kind. Thank you from the bottom of our hearts.  Please feel free to use any or all of this review.  Terry & Carrie Herman, Preston, CT</Review>

On March 12, 2021, I received an email from ADS, asking for the exact same authorization. I gave it, and asked why they were emailing when they texted for the same authorization ten days earlier.

On March 23, 2021, I called ADS to find out what was going on, because supplies were about to run out. I had to wait on hold for over TWO HOURS before I finally got to speak to someone, and they couldn't figure out what was wrong with the order.

<Review>**FINAL UPDATE**
At first, I was very unhappy with ADS customer service for the reasons below. However, ADS was extremely proactive in remedying the situation and now I am extremely satisfied. As soon as my insurance approved the authorization, ADS got my order ready and out the door. I believe that my initial experience was not representative of ADS as a whole and I applaud their customer service department for going above and beyond to make sure I could get my supplies as fast as possible.

**UPDATE**
So, I'm actually really impressed with ADS customer service! Less than one day after I posted the original review, a rep contacted me and helped me get everything sorted out. It turns out we do need some more paperwork (which I found a little frustrating, because I was told multiple times by multiple reps that they had all the paperwork necessary and all I had to do was wait), but hopefully that was the last of the miscommunication. They also apologized for the lack of communication on behalf of the company and even offered to overnight me some testing materials so that I can check my blood sugars in the meantime. This interaction makes me hopeful that my previous experience with ADS was not representative of their customer service. I don't like leaving bad reviews on yelp, but I think that a company that deals with life-saving medical supplies should be held to a higher standard than say, a coffee shop. I will update this review hopefully just one more time after everything works out and I actually get my G6 system!

I've been trying to get on the Dexcom G6 and my experience with Advanced Diabetes Supply has extremely been frustrating. The process of getting the supplies I need has been delayed multiple times because different reps keep giving me the wrong information. They even sent a text message that an authorization had been submitted, but when I called to check in, it actually had not been submitted. To their credit, every rep I spoke to has been very friendly. My experience is detailed below:

ADS: "We spoke with your doctor's office yesterday, we have all the paperwork, and everything looks good. We'll give you a call when things are ready."

Me: *calls to check in two weeks later*

ADS: "Actually, we need your doctor's office to send us a form so we can send it to your insurance. After we get that, it'll take about a week for your insurance to approve it."

Me: ??? then why did you tell me everything was good and have me wait two weeks for nothing??? *Has doctor submit necessary paperwork in less than one day. calls ADS to check in a week later."

ADS: "Yes, we have all the paperwork and we just have to submit an authorization to your insurance. I'll submit it now, check back in a few days."

**They actually sent me a text message which states that the authorization was submitted as urgent and everything should be approved in about a week.

Me: *calls back a few days later to check AGAIN*

ADS: "Your authorization hasn't been submitted.... Yes, I see that someone sent you that text message, but they didn't actually submit the authorization. I'll submit it now and everything should be ready in about a week."

Me: ??????? Your company literally sent me a text message that my authorization had been submitted as "URGENT" and that I would only have to wait another week. Now my process of waiting a week is starting over??

< Review>
ADS became my new provider of diabetes test strips in the summer of 2016 and it took months to get my strips.  Clearly the company was overwhelmed and did not have the staff to run this program effectively.  I spent hours calling and emailing to get the strips.  I ran out of supplies twice.  Finally when I decided it must be a fradulent company, I sent letters to the appropriate agencies.  Then a Sales person from ADS
called me and sent my strips but also many other products that I did not need or never use at a great cost to medicare my insurance and me.  And now I also have a pile of supplies that I will never use.  What a waste!!!</Review>

< Text>
I usually only write positive reviews, but my experience with Advanced Diabetes Supply has been so frustrating that I just had to write a negative review.  First of all, getting someone on the phone is nearly impossible.  If you leave a message, it takes days for them to return your call.  I am a Type 1 diabetic that uses an insulin pump and must check my blood sugar 8 times a day.  Even with sending BG logs and office visit chart notes, I have never been able to be approved to get the number of test strips needed.  This last time, after talking with someone at ADS at least daily for 2 weeks and my doctor faxing the same information to them at least 4 times, I have transferred my prescription to WalMart.  If you use an insulin pump and are on Medicare Part B to cover your diabetes supplies, do not waste your time on Advanced Diabetes Supply!<//Text>

<rate>5<//rate><Review>I was walking through Brand Blvd and I was curious about this place because of the name.  It said "rice ball" on the menu and I was instantly curious to try it out.  I tried the beef and spicy pork rice ball.  The  presentation of the rice ball was so cute.  It's actually not a ball, but rather a compact triangle.  The spicy pork was decent, but I really liked the beef rice ball.  The meat was seasoned in a Korean style as if I was eating KBBQ, but made into a Japanese dish.  With a two or three of the rice balls you can have a filling meal.

Don't forget to check in to get your free fountain drink.  You'll need it to wash down your rice balls.< /Review><Pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMZqXzTkQlUxEzLrU8AmWspGE-QyGWA6k9S0m1S=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMyGSnsXTJQ2zGMWGITG20wsugzBPkB0FB8s7kM=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipP0bbZf4KAzIUJM96h0yuDkYg8eMckQDQ7IdE6a=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipO-oS3k4kSRSLoP3CFVCIKBZmRlPyIrT1DKis-h=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPcX7fKmajxCuKRZfYYhVnfY8Foj-ZwWrBq1HVY=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPyiLMmCQOi7pwLW-p57kpF3aks1lIckpw7EspR=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPrfdd7HQHFt6IYOUF-4aZGfO-etDQCKJtR3Rip=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]< /Pictures><response>None< /response>< Gmap_id>

< review>
This place is the perfect lunch spot, if you're in the area. Very simple, easy to understand menu with good prices. Usually plenty of seating, and I've never been kept waiting for my food.
I usually get the curry chicken, salmon, or spicy shrimp rice balls. The crab is pretty good too. Don't get the tuna expecting sushi quality tuna-- it's more like cooked tuna from a can.
Arguably the best quick bite in Glendale. I could go here every week.< /review>

<review>Before i discovered this place, I was always craving mama masubi but having to wait until there was a food festival or something going on in the area.

In comes Gam Tu Bop. I appreciate that there's now a fixed location for one of my favorite foods. Also, compared to all of the other rice balls I've tried from various vendors, this place puts in a generous amount of stuffing into their product. The first time I tried this place,  I was very pleasantly surprised because I was accustomed to only getting a little bit of filling (I wasn't happy about the little amount and always thought they should put more given the prices, but that's what I was used to). So far I've only tried the mushroom and salmon teriyaki - salmon being my favorite one. I always get the seaweed to wrap it on the side so that it doesn't get soggy.

Needless to say after I discovered this place, I have no longer purchased rice balls from other vendors.<//review>< Gmap_id>

< Date>
1559836335764</Date>
<rating>5<//rating><Text>When I lived around here, this was one of my go-to places to eat. Each onigiri are ~$3 each and they don't skimp on the filling. I always compare onigiri to this place because they have the best filling to rice ratio. Here's a short description of all the different ones I've tried since they're all 5/5:
- Crab meat: they use the standard imitation crab so it's like eating a California sushi roll.
- Tuna: this reminds me of the tuna sandwiches that my grandpa would make me so there's just a lot of nostalgia
- Beef: the beef is in a sweet yet savory sauce that comes out nice and warm
- Grilled salmon: this salmon is cooked and flakey, much like the tuna one
- Spicy pork: reminds me of the spicy pork you get at Korean restaurants

This is definitely a great place to go if you want a quick and filling bite to eat. I've really missed this place since moving and I try to eat here anytime I'm in the area</Text>< pictures>

< review>
Gam tu bop is a really great place for food---one of my favorite in Glendale. They specialize in Onigiri, or Japanese rice balls. They're more or less just triangles of rice with different fillings inside of them, with options like beef, teriyaki chicken, eel, and scrambled egg. They're all tasty but the teriyaki chicken is my favorite. If you haven't been yet, give it a shot! Their prices are very reasonable.< /review>

I love eating rice balls and Gam Tu Bop has one of the best tasting rice balls. Not only they are delicious but very affordable. It's perfect for a quick lunch or dinner.

The rice balls come with different fillings and are sprinkled with Furikake seasoning which gives it that delicious taste. My favorites are the salmon, beef and unagi rice rolls. You cannot just eat one roll but eating two or three will definitely fill you up.<//text>

< Text>
Great little hidden gem. This is a small quaint place. They have bar and dining tables. I came with a group of about 8 and everyone seemed to be satisfied. Some ordered the nachos which seemed to be pretty popular. Others didn't the Mama's enchiladas. I had the enchiladas and they were very good and flavorful. I would recommend getting either one if you were to go. You can't go wrong with either one. My only downside is that they don't have fountain drinks< /Text>

< name>
Raymond Evans< /name>
<pictures>None</pictures>< Review>
Yesterday I called Burgundy Room to inquire about the price of just peanut sauce and the cucumber sauce that accompanies Satay as I had leftovers from another distant place and only needed the sauces.  The lady i spoke to said 6.99 for 16 ounces for each or 4.99 for 8 ounces.  I only needed the half size, so sent my caregiver to order and pickup.....I had even written down on the list what had been quoted.  When my caregiver returned home I was astounded to see I had been charged 13.06 for both and couldn't even read the light print on the receipt.....at that price I could have just ordered the Satay and what comes with it.  I called and asked for the manager.....I was told the manager wouldn't be there for a couple of hours, so I left my information.  Shortly thereafter, Lin called me back and said the original lady I had talked to "didn't know anything"........so why did she give me information?  Then Lin and I argued/talked over each other as I tried to make my point as a customer.  Language difficulties also cause problems but when dealing with the public businesses need to be fluent.  To add insult to injury, the peanut sauce was runny and bland, not the usual taste of the spices used, and, the cucumber "sauce" turned out to be a cucumber salad in a small Styrofoam container with tons of cut up cucumber, a few pieces of red onion, lettuce and the sauce in a very tiny container.  Most Thai restaurants have small pieces of cucumber and red onion IN the sauce.  So disappointing.  Lin offered to have the food returned for money back.......what an insult, not accommodating at all and I will never send anyone there again.......p.s. my caregiver's pineapple fried rice was bland and more like steamed rice than fried.  This restaurant is also extremely expensive compared to others.</Review>

<Review>This is one of those places that I never mean to end up at, but when I do I'm not mad about it. Kind of reminds me of bars from the Midwest (the dark bar + classic rock + booth combo), but with pricier drinks and more eccentric people to watch. This is usually my last stop of the night so I don't order anything too special--the tequila soda with extra lime is very generous in the lime department.

It gets busy in here at the weekends, so if you're looking for a more chill dive bar situation (and maybe access to one of the ragged but somehow kind of romantic booths), stop in on a weeknight. There are usually DJs here spinning obscure stuff or the aforementioned classic rock, which I'm here for. There are sometimes creeps and jerks here, but that's just Hollywood, baby!<//Review>< gmap_id>

< review>
From the minute I walked into the store the experience was horrible!!!! There were things out of place, returns or go backs at the registers, even the staff looked disheveled and unhealthy, as though maybe it's something in the water,  I'd have a better chance asking Google where something was in the store as she would know better than one of the staff who were, incredibly rude.  The only thing worse than there obvious distate for life in general made me feel as I was a child bothering my obviously preoccupied parent.  It was as though I was interrupting their busy conversation about their deviant new years romp with a fellow employee.  A cashier, whose name I will spare from the review for the sake of personal embarrassment couldn't even properly calculate the change I was due back because I had thrown in another dime at the last moment.   She finally broke down and got her phone out for something non Facebook related  and knocked the dust off the calculator app to finally provide me with my change (still 12 cents off) It is in this Shoppers honest opinion that my 11 year old daughter would be more qualified to work there and until she does I'll gladly take my business and my burdensome requests to Petco.< /review>

<Date>1447712814267</Date><Rate>5<//Rate>< review>
This is a great store for all your pet needs. They really have a huge variety of animal supplies here and they offer pet adoption on Saturdays. I've seen quite a few animals here on the adoption days.

Another thing I like about this store is the sales. Every time I've been in the store, they're having a sale. I think I've bought one item in the 20 times I've been there, that wasn't on sale. The prices are very reasonable and I would say they slightly edge out Petco in this department.

The return policy is great as well. I returned an item without a receipt and they were able to find the purchase through my Petsmart Rewards account. The employees went above and beyond to help me. They even offered my dog a cookie!<//review>
